Hi Karnan,
(The original question was mistakenly sent to the wrong address.  I'm re-sending my reply here, as well as attaching Karnan's original attachments.)

The section that you need in the documentation is here, http://ferret.pmel.noaa.gov/Ferret/documentation/users-guide/data-set-basics/ASCII-DATA. There are 3 steps to reading ascii data in ferret:
  • Decide what the grid of the variable(s) should be
  • Define that grid with DEFINE AXIS and DEFINE GRID commands
  • Initialize the data set with a FILE command.
Your data has 1 variable, along with longitude and latitude variables that will guide you in defining the grid.  For this kind of data, which represents data on a rectangular grid, there is an FAQ,

http://ferret.pmel.noaa.gov/Ferret/faq/reading-ascii-data-representing-a-grid

which should help you get started with your file.

Once you have the commands to read your data, then the FILL  or SHADE commands are the ones to use for a 2-D color plot.  You may also want to use SET VARIABLE/UNITS="units string"/TITLE="title string" so that your plot will be self-documenting.  Please give it a try. You are welcome to write back once you have a start, if you have questions. Show the commands you have tried and let us know what the question is.

If you are new to Ferret, please explore the Tutorials section of the main Documentation page to start familiarizing you with how to work with Ferret.

Ansley
